newsitem.title: UK: NWE naphtha ends higher on gasoline, Asian demand.
newsitem.headline: NWE naphtha ends higher on gasoline, Asian demand.

text.p: NWE naphtha moved higher on Monday in line with stronger gasoline and healthy Asian demand, but traders said most activity had centred on the swaps market with little physical trading done.
April naphtha swaps were reported done in the $208.50 to $209.50 cif NWE range.
On the physical side, traders said pipeline spec for March 27 to April 3 delivery was heard bid at $202/$205.
Prices for non-pipeline cargoes were assessed around $195/$200 a tonne cif NWE.
A 35,000 tonne cargo was reported to be on offer out of Antwerp having loaded at the weekend.
Despite the lack of activity traders said crude's gains on Friday as well as a jump in prices in the Asian market had given the market a more positive tone.
On the Tokyo market, first-half May open-spec naphtha was assessed at about $235.50/$237.50 on Monday, up from Friday levels of $231.00/232.00.
